<title>USA: Harbinger buys remaining shares in unit.</title>
<headline>Harbinger buys remaining shares in unit.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Harbinger Corp on Thursday it had completed its purchase of the equity in its Harbinger NET Services subsidiary that it did not already own.</p>
<p>The deal was valued at $7.2 million.</p>
<p>In October, Harbinger said it planned to buy a 30 percent stake in Harbinger NET owned by BellSouth Telecommunications Inc and other shareholders.</p>
<p>Harbinger is a provider of electronic commerce with more than 23,000 billable subscribers and more than 39,500 active mailboxes on its global value-added network.</p>
